lead_paragraph: There have been a number of articles and blog posts lately claiming that Ireland is over the hump, that it's all coming right; see for example this recent piece by Henry Kaspar. But I was checking to see if it was still true that Icelandic CDS prices -- the cost of insuring against default -- were much lower than Ireland's. And given what we've been hearing, the Irish CDS story comes as something of a shock:
